<P>To circus_x:&nbsp; Many Chinese websites still use old character pages GB&nbsp;(Simplified) and Big5 (Traditional); many Japanese websites use the old Shift-JIS (Japan Industry Standard).&nbsp; But more and more will be in Unicode as the standard gains acceptance throughout the world.&nbsp; You can see some encodings under View/Encoding in the Explorer browser.&nbsp; "English" browsers can view Unicode.</P>
<P>I worked in the software industry and now, in some applications, it is becoming important for some programmers to know other human languages like Chinese and Japanese.</P>
